
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dscverify` baraye check kardane signature-haye Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) estefade mishavad. In dastoor komak mikonad ta az dorosti va etemadpazirboodane file-ha va etela'at اطمینان حاصل konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dscverify filename.pdf`  --> 📄 Check kardane signature-haye yek file PDF.
    🔹 `dscverify --help` --> ❓ Namayesh dadane rahnama va gozine-haye dastoor.
    🔹 `dscverify --version` --> ℹ️ Namayesh dadane version dastoor.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dscverify document.pdf

    🔹 Check kardane signature-haye file "document.pdf".

    $ dscverify report.xml

    🔹 Check kardane signature-haye file "report.xml".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dscverify my_contract.pdf
    Verification successful.

    🔹 In mesal نشان میدهد ke signature-haye file "my_contract.pdf" dorost va valid ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dscverify` command is used to verify Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) signatures. This command helps ensure the authenticity and integrity of files and data.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dscverify filename.pdf`  --> 📄 Verify the signatures of a PDF file.
    🔹 `dscverify --help` --> ❓ Display help information and command options.
    🔹 `dscverify --version` --> ℹ️ Display the command version.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dscverify document.pdf

    🔹 Verify the signatures of the file "document.pdf".

    $ dscverify report.xml

    🔹 Verify the signatures of the file "report.xml".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dscverify my_contract.pdf
    Verification successful.

    🔹 This example shows that the signatures of the file "my_contract.pdf" are valid and authentic.

